1
00:00:11,116 --> 00:00:13,160
[rock music playing]

2
00:00:43,148 --> 00:00:47,278
CHAPTER 39: USE A BIT OF SENSE
AND FIGURE IT OUT YOURSELF

3
00:00:47,361 --> 00:00:49,029
[Eui-ju panting]

4
00:00:49,113 --> 00:00:51,740
Mr. Ga! Mr. Ga. Wait, Mr. Ga.

5
00:00:51,824 --> 00:00:55,661
Sir, I have something to tell you!
Wait just a moment. Wait, Mr. Ga.

6
00:00:56,161 --> 00:00:58,205
Hold on. [panting]

7
00:01:01,208 --> 00:01:02,251
Just a second.

8
00:01:06,005 --> 00:01:07,006
What is it?

9
00:01:08,507 --> 00:01:11,427
[hopeful, tender music playing]

10
00:01:16,390 --> 00:01:17,725
I…

11
00:01:23,230 --> 00:01:24,231
I…

12
00:01:28,319 --> 00:01:30,654
The after-school class is too much for me!

13
00:01:32,489 --> 00:01:34,325
[owl hoots]

14
00:01:34,408 --> 00:01:36,076
[exhales heavily]

15
00:01:37,244 --> 00:01:38,245
What?

16
00:01:39,622 --> 00:01:40,956
[sighs] I…

17
00:01:41,999 --> 00:01:43,417
I keep…

18
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:44,919
[comical music playing]

19
00:01:45,002 --> 00:01:47,212
[sighs] …skipping my homework,

20
00:01:48,213 --> 00:01:51,342
and dragging the rest of the class down.

21
00:01:52,593 --> 00:01:54,637
It's emotionally exhausting.

22
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:56,889
This sense of guilt
is taking a toll on me.

23
00:01:58,098 --> 00:01:59,099
[sobs]

24
00:02:00,392 --> 00:02:02,686
Can't you find
any motivation to give math a shot?

25
00:02:02,770 --> 00:02:03,771
[pants]

26
00:02:03,854 --> 00:02:06,357
What happened to your promise
from ten years ago?

27
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:08,067
You sounded so sure back then.

28
00:02:08,651 --> 00:02:10,819
[stammers] Huh?

29
00:02:11,612 --> 00:02:14,365
I'm talking about you. Yeo Eui-ju.

30
00:02:18,035 --> 00:02:19,662
About me? Really?

31
00:02:20,788 --> 00:02:23,749
I had no doubt in my mind
that you'd be good at math.

32
00:02:28,045 --> 00:02:29,046
But…

33
00:02:30,130 --> 00:02:33,342
You said I made
a promise to you? What promise?

34
00:02:34,677 --> 00:02:35,678
Forget it.

35
00:02:37,471 --> 00:02:40,224
Huh? Mr. Ga. Hold on, please.

36
00:02:40,307 --> 00:02:41,308
EPISODE 13

37
00:02:41,392 --> 00:02:43,936
I don't understand
what kind of promise you're talking about.

38
00:02:44,019 --> 00:02:45,521
Mr. Ga! Oh.

39
00:02:47,147 --> 00:02:48,482
Did you clean the classroom?

40
00:02:48,565 --> 00:02:51,151
[stammers] I forgot.

41
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:55,990
Goodbye then.

42
00:02:59,660 --> 00:03:00,661
[huffs]

43
00:03:08,669 --> 00:03:10,879
[curious music playing]

44
00:03:15,342 --> 00:03:16,343
A promise?

45
00:03:17,261 --> 00:03:19,805
I don't think I can do it.

46
00:03:20,514 --> 00:03:22,224
I just can't do it.

47
00:03:22,307 --> 00:03:24,560
Then just write him a love letter.

48
00:03:24,643 --> 00:03:26,937
-A letter?
-Yes. You're a writer.

49
00:03:27,021 --> 00:03:28,647
Use your writing and confess.

50
00:03:30,315 --> 00:03:31,316
Confess?

51
00:03:34,319 --> 00:03:35,320
[ding plays]

52
00:03:35,988 --> 00:03:37,364
[mischievous music playing]

53
00:03:37,448 --> 00:03:39,366
WE WERE FRIENDS - EPISODE 9

54
00:03:42,369 --> 00:03:44,038
[scoffs]

55
00:03:44,121 --> 00:03:45,122
I'm here.

56
00:03:47,916 --> 00:03:51,628
Oh, I wonder why
I didn't think of this earlier. Huh?

57
00:03:53,005 --> 00:03:56,341
I can just confess my feelings
for him through my writing here.

58
00:03:56,925 --> 00:03:58,343
Eat up. I know you're hungry.

59
00:03:58,427 --> 00:03:59,720
This looks great.

60
00:04:04,683 --> 00:04:05,684
Did you choose me?

61
00:04:06,268 --> 00:04:09,063
Or do you just wanna get away
from Kang Tae-ha?

62
00:04:09,938 --> 00:04:12,149
-What's the difference?
-There's a huge difference!

63
00:04:15,778 --> 00:04:17,696
I don't wanna be someone's refuge.

64
00:04:18,572 --> 00:04:20,908
It's just too painful to think of Tae-ha.

65
00:04:21,742 --> 00:04:24,620
But I feel a little more at ease
when I'm with you.

66
00:04:24,703 --> 00:04:27,664
So, that's all I am to you?
A little bit of comfort.

67
00:04:29,333 --> 00:04:31,752
-That's harsh.
-[patrons murmuring]

68
00:04:32,419 --> 00:04:34,546
I'm sorry for being selfish.

69
00:04:34,630 --> 00:04:36,131
It's okay, I'm just as selfish.

70
00:04:37,174 --> 00:04:39,426
If I stay by your side
when you're confused,

71
00:04:39,510 --> 00:04:41,053
maybe you'll choose me in the end.

72
00:04:41,136 --> 00:04:44,890
IN THAT MOMENT,
YOON DECIDED TO SHOOT HIS SHOT

73
00:04:46,016 --> 00:04:47,559
Si-on, I like you.

74
00:04:48,685 --> 00:04:51,063
[comical, awkward music playing]

75
00:04:52,147 --> 00:04:53,148
[sighs]

76
00:04:54,942 --> 00:04:55,984
The truth is…

77
00:04:57,319 --> 00:05:00,697
I've had a crush on you for a long time.
Since we were in high school.

78
00:05:03,075 --> 00:05:04,159
[groans]

79
00:05:04,243 --> 00:05:07,913
If I don't tell you today,
I might just regret it forever.

80
00:05:11,875 --> 00:05:12,876
[sighs]

81
00:05:17,506 --> 00:05:19,883
How can you not see how I feel?
Isn't it obvious?

82
00:05:19,967 --> 00:05:23,220
Can't you just use some common sense
and figure it out on your own?

83
00:05:26,348 --> 00:05:27,391
I have feelings for you.

84
00:05:27,474 --> 00:05:28,851
Every time you see me…

85
00:05:29,852 --> 00:05:32,646
[gulps, stutters]
…my heart races like crazy.

86
00:05:33,772 --> 00:05:36,817
I get so nervous
when I see you or walk past you.

87
00:05:38,193 --> 00:05:39,278
It's happening right now.

88
00:05:39,903 --> 00:05:42,156
When you gave me a hard time
and were mean only to me,

89
00:05:42,239 --> 00:05:44,616
even when you embarrassed me
for being bad at math.

90
00:05:45,450 --> 00:05:46,910
I never hated you, you know?

91
00:05:47,786 --> 00:05:50,038
I like you. I like you.

92
00:05:50,122 --> 00:05:51,331
I like you, Ju Si-on!

93
00:05:52,166 --> 00:05:53,375
[shudders]

94
00:05:56,170 --> 00:05:57,171
[sighs]

95
00:05:57,254 --> 00:05:59,298
[patrons applauding]

96
00:06:05,012 --> 00:06:06,013
[chuckles]

97
00:06:07,347 --> 00:06:08,348
[sighs]

98
00:06:09,850 --> 00:06:12,311
So, you couldn't write the letter?

99
00:06:12,394 --> 00:06:16,064
[clicks tongue]
Well. Maybe I'll do it later.

100
00:06:16,148 --> 00:06:18,108
-Geez. When exactly?
-[chuckles]

101
00:06:19,109 --> 00:06:23,906
But I don't think
that It'll make any difference.

102
00:06:23,989 --> 00:06:27,576
Even if muster up the courage
to express my feelings for him,

103
00:06:27,659 --> 00:06:30,787
he obviously won't like me back.

104
00:06:32,122 --> 00:06:33,874
-Hello, Mr. Ga.
-Hello, Mr. Ga.

105
00:06:33,957 --> 00:06:35,334
Hello, Mr. Ga.

106
00:06:38,629 --> 00:06:40,339
[student] Did you see that?

107
00:06:40,422 --> 00:06:43,884
[whispering] Go on. Go on.
Come on, go talk to him.

108
00:06:45,344 --> 00:06:46,511
Mr. Ga.

109
00:06:46,595 --> 00:06:47,763
[stammers, clears throat]

110
00:06:47,846 --> 00:06:49,181
[sniffles] Di…

111
00:06:49,264 --> 00:06:52,434
Did you perhaps read the new episode
that I posted yesterday?

112
00:06:53,143 --> 00:06:54,645
[stutters] What did you think?

113
00:06:54,728 --> 00:06:56,521
[comical music playing]

114
00:06:56,605 --> 00:06:58,398
Choi Yoon's sudden change seemed off.

115
00:06:59,691 --> 00:07:01,652
Why would he say that? It was too random.

116
00:07:08,242 --> 00:07:09,243
What's wrong?

117
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,828
What? What did he say?

118
00:07:12,329 --> 00:07:13,330
Nothing.

119
00:07:14,915 --> 00:07:16,625
-[sniffles] Let's go.
-Huh?

120
00:07:18,752 --> 00:07:20,796
[class] Good morning!

121
00:07:21,964 --> 00:07:23,632
Did everyone bring
their homework assignments?

122
00:07:23,715 --> 00:07:25,133
[class] Yes.

123
00:07:25,217 --> 00:07:27,844
[Woo-su] Don't think about finishing
them now. Please turn them in.

124
00:07:27,928 --> 00:07:29,304
[students] Okay.

125
00:07:30,222 --> 00:07:31,265
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

126
00:07:40,023 --> 00:07:41,066
[giggling]

127
00:07:43,110 --> 00:07:44,361
Who didn't do it?

128
00:07:47,281 --> 00:07:48,532
Me.

129
00:07:50,117 --> 00:07:51,118
Stand up.

130
00:07:56,039 --> 00:07:57,291
Why didn't you do it?

131
00:07:58,208 --> 00:07:59,751
I forgot about it.

132
00:08:00,502 --> 00:08:01,503
You forgot?

133
00:08:02,170 --> 00:08:04,006
How could you forget doing it?

134
00:08:04,089 --> 00:08:07,134
What's your priority among all the things
you have to do? Isn't it studying?

135
00:08:07,217 --> 00:08:08,844
And doing homework?

136
00:08:10,095 --> 00:08:11,596
Are you gonna keep this up?

137
00:08:13,181 --> 00:08:14,182
No, sir.

138
00:08:14,266 --> 00:08:16,226
Add more problems
to the assignment you didn't do,

139
00:08:16,310 --> 00:08:17,769
and bring it in by tomorrow.

140
00:08:19,146 --> 00:08:20,147
Yes, sir.

141
00:08:20,230 --> 00:08:21,231
Sit down.

142
00:08:27,112 --> 00:08:28,280
Turn to page 99.

143
00:08:28,363 --> 00:08:32,159
[whispers] Did you do something wrong?
Why is he so harsh on you?

144
00:08:33,327 --> 00:08:35,620
I don't know. I'm screwed.

145
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:42,294
Why do you think math is so strict?

146
00:08:42,377 --> 00:08:43,670
CHAPTER 40:
YOU THINK YOU COULD HIDE IT?

147
00:08:43,754 --> 00:08:47,507
He says there will never be partial points
for any of the math quizzes we take. Ugh.

148
00:08:47,591 --> 00:08:50,761
[sighs] He's cold-blooded after all.
He's like an AI.

149
00:08:52,429 --> 00:08:55,140
He's just doing it his way, isn't he?

150
00:08:55,223 --> 00:08:56,600
That might actually be fair.

151
00:08:57,267 --> 00:08:59,144
What're you talking about?

152
00:08:59,227 --> 00:09:01,563
So what if he has a handsome face?

153
00:09:01,646 --> 00:09:03,315
My point, exactly.

154
00:09:03,398 --> 00:09:07,361
That's what makes him even more annoying,
you know? He looks like a prince.

155
00:09:07,444 --> 00:09:10,614
But his personality is nasty as hell.
It really kills the fantasy.

156
00:09:10,697 --> 00:09:14,242
His personality is not that nasty.
He's just a little cranky.

157
00:09:20,207 --> 00:09:23,293
That's weird for you to say. Huh?
You used to talk crap about him.

158
00:09:24,169 --> 00:09:26,213
Why are you on his side now?

159
00:09:28,715 --> 00:09:30,884
I did? When did I?

160
00:09:30,967 --> 00:09:31,968
[chuckles]

161
00:09:32,803 --> 00:09:34,012
Nuh-uh.

162
00:09:35,389 --> 00:09:38,183
Do you maybe… have a crush on him?

163
00:09:38,266 --> 00:09:39,267
[amusing music playing]

164
00:09:39,351 --> 00:09:40,352
Huh?

165
00:09:41,812 --> 00:09:44,981
Hey! Watch what you say now.

166
00:09:45,065 --> 00:09:46,441
She's not crazy.

167
00:09:47,150 --> 00:09:48,610
[chuckles] Right?

168
00:09:48,693 --> 00:09:50,862
[chuckles] I went too far, didn't I?

169
00:09:50,946 --> 00:09:53,865
-Yeah, you crossed the line.
-I'm sorry. My bad.

170
00:09:53,949 --> 00:09:55,534
[laughs] Time to go. We're off, Eui-ju.

171
00:09:59,704 --> 00:10:01,498
Goodness.

172
00:10:01,581 --> 00:10:04,126
Love and cough
can never be hidden, you know?

173
00:10:04,209 --> 00:10:07,671
[whispers] You think they know?
They couldn't have noticed it, could they?

174
00:10:07,754 --> 00:10:09,965
[sighs] I have to be careful.

175
00:10:12,384 --> 00:10:15,303
Don't you think that web novel
is based on our school?

176
00:10:15,387 --> 00:10:17,806
-You think?
-The characters are like our teachers.

177
00:10:17,889 --> 00:10:21,309
Kang Tae-ha is the PE teacher
and the rich one is the Japanese teacher.

178
00:10:21,393 --> 00:10:22,811
Here, check this out.

179
00:10:23,603 --> 00:10:27,399
"A beige cardigan on his shoulders and
an old brown leather watch on his wrist."

180
00:10:27,482 --> 00:10:30,318
-This is the Korean lit teacher.
-[gasps] You're right.

181
00:10:30,402 --> 00:10:33,155
Actually, I saw him wearing
that same cardigan today.

182
00:10:33,238 --> 00:10:36,158
-I'm telling you.
-And it's the same for math too.

183
00:10:36,241 --> 00:10:40,829
I saw him lift his pinky finger when
he pushed up his glasses in math class.

184
00:10:40,912 --> 00:10:42,414
-Five out of five times.
-Seriously?

185
00:10:42,497 --> 00:10:43,999
-[gasps]
-That's exactly like Ju Si-on.

186
00:10:44,082 --> 00:10:45,876
I'm rooting for Ju Si-on and Choi Yoon.

187
00:10:45,959 --> 00:10:47,794
I'm rooting for Kang Tae-ha and Choi Yoon.

188
00:10:47,878 --> 00:10:48,879
WE WERE FRIENDS

189
00:10:48,962 --> 00:10:52,382
[Ha-su, softly] Ju Si-on.
Kang Tae-ha. Choi Yoon?

190
00:10:53,216 --> 00:10:54,843
…AND TURNS HIS WATCH
TO LOOK AT IT

191
00:11:05,270 --> 00:11:06,771
"Then Si-on says,

192
00:11:06,855 --> 00:11:08,899
-"When a single star is born…"
-"When a single star is born,

193
00:11:08,982 --> 00:11:13,528
a massive cloud of dust surrounds it,
blinding everything in sight."

194
00:11:13,612 --> 00:11:17,032
[both] "That's why people say
stars are born out of chaos."

195
00:11:17,115 --> 00:11:20,702
This problem seems complicated,
but it's simple once you solve it.

196
00:11:20,785 --> 00:11:23,538
No math problem can be
more complex than life,

197
00:11:23,622 --> 00:11:25,081
no matter how difficult it is.

198
00:11:26,875 --> 00:11:29,669
[Ha-su] This is… exactly what Mr. Ga said.

199
00:11:30,378 --> 00:11:32,672
Could someone in my class be writing this?

200
00:11:32,756 --> 00:11:34,549
If she is, it means…

201
00:11:35,592 --> 00:11:37,886
she's also in the after-school program?

202
00:11:37,969 --> 00:11:39,262
Ms. Yeo, put some heart into it.

203
00:11:39,346 --> 00:11:41,806
-I want actual emotion.
-Come on, she can't say that.

204
00:11:41,890 --> 00:11:43,225
Your drawing must be pretty bad

205
00:11:43,308 --> 00:11:45,352
-for her to react like this.
-When it comes to drawing, you see…

206
00:11:46,269 --> 00:11:50,106
-What do you know about drawing?
-Okay, my bad, Ms. Art Teacher.

207
00:11:50,190 --> 00:11:52,275
Yeah, whatever.

208
00:11:52,359 --> 00:11:55,737
-I couldn't believe that when she told me…
-No way!

209
00:11:56,488 --> 00:11:58,698
-[gasps]
-What is it, Jenny?

210
00:11:58,782 --> 00:12:00,617
-Are you reading something?
-This is great.

211
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:03,328
-Fifty Shades of Mr. CEO.
-[gasps, squeals]

212
00:12:03,912 --> 00:12:06,248
The male lead
finally confessed his feelings!

213
00:12:06,331 --> 00:12:07,332
[gasps] That's insane. How?

214
00:12:07,415 --> 00:12:10,794
He went wild. Like this. Pow!

215
00:12:10,877 --> 00:12:12,045
-[gasps]
-[clears throat]

216
00:12:12,671 --> 00:12:14,673
"You know I need you by my side."

217
00:12:14,756 --> 00:12:16,883
-[Yeong-jae laughs]
-"You can't quit."

218
00:12:16,967 --> 00:12:18,552
[both squeal]

219
00:12:19,344 --> 00:12:20,804
The comments say the female lead

220
00:12:20,887 --> 00:12:23,098
will go to the male lead's house
in the next episode.

221
00:12:23,181 --> 00:12:26,935
Maybe he'll act like he's sick.
It's a totally obvious trick.

222
00:12:27,018 --> 00:12:30,981
[breathes deeply] But those clichés
work well despite how obvious they are.

223
00:12:31,064 --> 00:12:32,065
-Exactly?
-Mmm.

224
00:12:32,148 --> 00:12:34,276
[Jenny] Why is it so exciting
when it's so cringy?

225
00:12:34,359 --> 00:12:37,112
Romance novels are a guilty pleasure.

226
00:12:37,195 --> 00:12:39,406
-You just can't resist!
-I know!

227
00:12:40,031 --> 00:12:43,785
Those amazing writers' pieces
are all kinda the same in a way, right?

228
00:12:43,868 --> 00:12:45,412
What is it?
Are you stuck with your writing?

229
00:12:45,495 --> 00:12:46,746
You said you finished it.

230
00:12:46,830 --> 00:12:48,290
What if becomes a mega hit?

231
00:12:49,124 --> 00:12:51,459
Mega hit? [chuckles]

232
00:12:51,543 --> 00:12:54,296
Aw, you'll be
the first to hear the news, then.

233
00:12:54,379 --> 00:12:55,463
[Ha-su] That's right.

234
00:12:58,133 --> 00:13:00,594
Yeah, I'm at school.
It's all right, I can talk.

235
00:13:02,178 --> 00:13:04,097
Oh, the movie we watched that day?

236
00:13:04,180 --> 00:13:05,181
I remember.

237
00:13:05,849 --> 00:13:08,393
A sequel? [chuckles] Are you serious?

238
00:13:10,020 --> 00:13:12,606
[sighs] He must be talking to that woman.

239
00:13:13,315 --> 00:13:16,192
[chuckles] I haven't watched it.

240
00:13:16,276 --> 00:13:17,652
What's so funny now?

241
00:13:23,116 --> 00:13:24,117
[sniffles]

242
00:13:26,036 --> 00:13:28,413
[downcast music playing]

243
00:13:30,248 --> 00:13:33,877
What's your priority among all the things
you have to do? Isn't it studying?

244
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:35,170
And doing homework?

245
00:13:35,253 --> 00:13:36,379
[chuckles]

246
00:13:38,548 --> 00:13:40,216
Why would he say that? It was too random.

247
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:41,301
[laughs]

248
00:13:52,228 --> 00:13:55,940
He's never given me that kind of smile,
not even for a second.

249
00:13:59,402 --> 00:14:01,237
So, this is L-O-V-E?

250
00:14:01,321 --> 00:14:02,322
[scoffs]

251
00:14:03,281 --> 00:14:05,241
How could you live
through this every time?

252
00:14:06,159 --> 00:14:08,578
Even now, it still hurts so much.

253
00:14:08,662 --> 00:14:10,872
Growing pains are inevitable.

254
00:14:13,208 --> 00:14:14,209
Ugh.

255
00:14:15,168 --> 00:14:17,253
I wish it were all just part of a novel.

256
00:14:18,171 --> 00:14:19,923
Then, I'd do everything as I wanted.

257
00:14:21,174 --> 00:14:23,385
From the confession
all the way to the ending.

258
00:14:24,928 --> 00:14:26,596
I'd just have it all go my way.

259
00:14:27,847 --> 00:14:30,558
So, are you just gonna give up?

260
00:14:30,642 --> 00:14:31,643
[clicks tongue]

261
00:14:32,185 --> 00:14:34,979
What's there to give up
when I didn't even start it?

262
00:14:36,272 --> 00:14:40,151
What did I tell you?
L-O-V-E has no detours.

263
00:14:41,403 --> 00:14:43,488
Nah. [breathes deeply]

264
00:14:45,198 --> 00:14:46,408
I choose to stop.

265
00:14:48,451 --> 00:14:50,203
I want to stop here, Go-ya.

266
00:14:51,746 --> 00:14:53,373
If I keep going like this,

267
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:59,045
I feel like I'll get hit by a bicycle
and a car going 86 miles per hour.

268
00:14:59,671 --> 00:15:01,589
I might just end up being a bloody mess.

269
00:15:04,342 --> 00:15:06,177
It's already too hard for me.

270
00:15:08,596 --> 00:15:09,889
I choose to give up.

271
00:15:13,977 --> 00:15:15,979
In his eyes, she's a real woman.

272
00:15:16,062 --> 00:15:17,063
But I'm not.

273
00:15:18,523 --> 00:15:19,524
[sniffles]

274
00:15:20,525 --> 00:15:22,402
That will never change
no matter what I do.

275
00:15:24,154 --> 00:15:25,238
And most of all,

276
00:15:26,906 --> 00:15:28,199
he looks really happy.

277
00:15:29,659 --> 00:15:31,786
[chuckles] Isn't that what matters?

278
00:15:35,832 --> 00:15:36,916
[whispering] Seriously…

279
00:15:38,543 --> 00:15:40,128
[sobs, sniffles]

280
00:15:42,589 --> 00:15:44,299
[inhales sharply, sighs]

281
00:15:50,764 --> 00:15:52,182
Mmm, this is delicious.

282
00:15:53,892 --> 00:15:55,935
Hey. Where were you today?

283
00:15:57,479 --> 00:15:59,773
Did you meet up
with that friend of yours, Na Deul-i?

284
00:15:59,856 --> 00:16:01,274
-[laughs]
-What're you talking about?

285
00:16:01,357 --> 00:16:02,484
She's back in Seoul.

286
00:16:03,026 --> 00:16:04,194
Nah, you're lying.

287
00:16:05,236 --> 00:16:06,821
I can tell you saw her.

288
00:16:07,614 --> 00:16:10,366
You're going out with her?
What is it? Tell me, come on.

289
00:16:11,034 --> 00:16:12,827
Did you decide to get back together? Huh?

290
00:16:12,911 --> 00:16:15,622
-Eat your food.
-He's changing the subject.

291
00:16:16,790 --> 00:16:19,334
What is it? Don't be shy.

292
00:16:20,001 --> 00:16:24,005
Are you embarrassed, dear? How cute.

293
00:16:24,088 --> 00:16:26,174
Hey, he said no, knock it off.

294
00:16:26,674 --> 00:16:28,802
-Just eat your food.
-Just think about it.

295
00:16:29,302 --> 00:16:31,471
So many girls approached him for his looks

296
00:16:31,554 --> 00:16:33,681
only to back away
once they got to know him.

297
00:16:33,765 --> 00:16:36,059
-Aw, poor them.
-Yeah. Tons of them.

298
00:16:36,142 --> 00:16:37,143
-Mmm.
-Yeah.

299
00:16:37,227 --> 00:16:40,688
I was worried that he might end up
with some crazy evil wizard

300
00:16:40,772 --> 00:16:43,274
that would just spend his entire life
throwing curses on Earth-- Ooh!

301
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:45,985
-Guys!
-Ugh, you're making a mess.

302
00:16:46,069 --> 00:16:48,446
Your moves are totally predictable.
It doesn't hurt at all!

303
00:16:48,530 --> 00:16:50,657
-Predict this, then!
-Guys, we're at the table!

304
00:16:50,740 --> 00:16:52,242
Stop acting like kids!

305
00:16:52,325 --> 00:16:55,078
-You can't avoid a single hit.
-I'm hitting you way more.

306
00:16:58,081 --> 00:16:59,916
-Yoon's confession is a twist.
-I didn't expect Yoon

307
00:16:59,999 --> 00:17:02,252
-to hit him with a confession.
-It's logically unexplainable,

308
00:17:02,335 --> 00:17:03,586
but emotionally perfect.

309
00:17:03,670 --> 00:17:05,255
[scoffs] See?

310
00:17:05,338 --> 00:17:07,715
Everyone likes his confession.

311
00:17:07,799 --> 00:17:10,009
It's not random. [chuckles]

312
00:17:16,641 --> 00:17:19,227
[commentor] Maybe the writer
goes to Murim Girls' High.

313
00:17:19,310 --> 00:17:22,146
[unsettling music playing]

314
00:17:22,230 --> 00:17:23,481
[gasps]

315
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:28,111
What… What the heck? [breathes shakily]

316
00:17:28,194 --> 00:17:30,238
Does she go to my school?

317
00:17:31,072 --> 00:17:32,699
She was probably just saying it, right?

318
00:17:32,782 --> 00:17:34,909
-[breathes shakily]
-[phone chimes]

319
00:17:34,993 --> 00:17:35,994
Who's still awake? Huh?

320
00:17:36,077 --> 00:17:37,078
11TH GRADE CLASS 2 GROUP CHAT
DAN-JI

321
00:17:38,454 --> 00:17:41,332
[sighing, breathing shakily]

322
00:17:55,430 --> 00:17:56,931
[students chattering]

323
00:18:03,104 --> 00:18:05,899
DOES THE WRITER
GO TO MURIM GIRLS' HIGH?

324
00:18:07,317 --> 00:18:08,776
Do you read web novels?

325
00:18:08,860 --> 00:18:10,403
[student] No, not these days.

326
00:18:11,237 --> 00:18:14,741
-Do you read them too?
-[chuckles] I'm not talking about me.

327
00:18:14,824 --> 00:18:16,618
There's this web novel
with main characters

328
00:18:16,701 --> 00:18:19,412
who are almost identical
to our Korean literature,

329
00:18:19,495 --> 00:18:22,165
math, PE, and Japanese language teachers.

330
00:18:22,248 --> 00:18:23,791
What? Seriously?

331
00:18:24,834 --> 00:18:26,711
One of the main characters
is a math genius.

332
00:18:26,794 --> 00:18:31,299
And his personality is just like
our homeroom teacher. Isn't it crazy?

333
00:18:31,382 --> 00:18:32,967
-Our math teacher? I know.
-No way.

334
00:18:33,051 --> 00:18:36,346
Ugh, I'm dying to know who the writer is.

335
00:18:36,429 --> 00:18:38,973
If it were me,
I wouldn't be able to keep it a secret.

336
00:18:39,933 --> 00:18:41,392
What do you think, Eui-ju?

337
00:18:43,853 --> 00:18:45,438
About what?

338
00:18:45,521 --> 00:18:47,607
If it were you,
would you be able to hide it?

339
00:18:49,484 --> 00:18:50,693
Hide what?

340
00:18:53,071 --> 00:18:55,823
What's with that straight face?
I was just asking.

341
00:18:58,785 --> 00:18:59,786
[scoffs]

342
00:19:01,412 --> 00:19:02,664
Oh, who could it be?

343
00:19:17,220 --> 00:19:19,847
[Eui-ju] She sounded like
she already knew everything.

344
00:19:19,931 --> 00:19:21,474
[chattering]

345
00:19:21,557 --> 00:19:23,184
It's good. Mmm.

346
00:19:23,267 --> 00:19:25,144
Did you hand in the math assignment? Huh?

347
00:19:27,188 --> 00:19:29,482
Should I just ask her to keep it a secret?

348
00:19:30,149 --> 00:19:32,735
What if I do
and she lets the entire school know?

349
00:19:32,819 --> 00:19:34,070
What do I do now?

350
00:19:34,988 --> 00:19:36,030
Huh?

351
00:19:36,739 --> 00:19:38,741
I asked about the math assignment.

352
00:19:38,825 --> 00:19:41,327
You might get demerits
if you don't turn it in.

353
00:19:41,411 --> 00:19:43,746
Oh. Right, I should.

354
00:19:43,830 --> 00:19:45,164
I'll do it later today.

355
00:19:45,748 --> 00:19:48,084
Eui-ju. Eui-ju, don't forget, okay?

356
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:49,168
[chuckles]

357
00:19:51,629 --> 00:19:53,548
What's wrong? You okay?

358
00:19:53,631 --> 00:19:54,632
Uh-huh.

359
00:19:55,675 --> 00:19:57,760
[Dan-ji] This rolled omelet is so good.

360
00:19:59,345 --> 00:20:01,514
[pensive music playing]

361
00:20:01,597 --> 00:20:03,349
[inhales deeply, sighs]

362
00:20:08,354 --> 00:20:09,355
[breathes shakily]

363
00:20:10,481 --> 00:20:13,026
One of the main characters
is a math genius.

364
00:20:13,109 --> 00:20:16,237
And his personality is just like
our homeroom teacher.

365
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:17,321
Isn't it crazy?

366
00:20:18,031 --> 00:20:19,323
What do you think, Eui-ju?

367
00:20:20,575 --> 00:20:22,368
If it were you,
would you be able to hide it?

368
00:20:22,994 --> 00:20:25,997
Ugh. What if everyone knows
by the time I get there tomorrow?

369
00:20:26,080 --> 00:20:27,999
[sighs, exhales sharply]

370
00:20:37,759 --> 00:20:38,885
[groans, sniffles]

371
00:20:41,512 --> 00:20:42,513
[PA chiming]

372
00:20:42,597 --> 00:20:44,682
CHAPTER 41:
NOTHING STAYS A SECRET FOREVER

373
00:20:44,766 --> 00:20:47,351
-[student 1] Hey, hurry over here.
-She fell asleep during class again.

374
00:20:47,435 --> 00:20:49,395
You went to the cafeteria, didn't you?

375
00:20:49,479 --> 00:20:51,689
[student 1] I didn't hear from you
all night long.

376
00:20:51,773 --> 00:20:54,317
Yeah! Oh my God, we had so much fun.

377
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:56,652
Yeah, we drove in the park, and then we…

378
00:20:56,736 --> 00:20:58,905
-Hello.
-[class] Hello.

379
00:21:02,450 --> 00:21:05,078
All right. We're starting
Gongmudohaga today, right?

380
00:21:05,161 --> 00:21:07,038
Please turn to page 168.

381
00:21:07,747 --> 00:21:08,998
Mr. Yoon.

382
00:21:09,791 --> 00:21:10,792
Yes?

383
00:21:10,875 --> 00:21:12,877
Is she going to expose it during class?

384
00:21:13,711 --> 00:21:14,921
She wouldn't.

385
00:21:15,004 --> 00:21:18,299
-So, is everything up to here on the exam?
-Yes, that's right.

386
00:21:24,013 --> 00:21:26,808
Are you okay?
You're up to something, aren't you?

387
00:21:27,642 --> 00:21:28,643
Nah.

388
00:21:30,061 --> 00:21:32,105
[Yoon] "My love, do not cross that river."

389
00:21:32,772 --> 00:21:35,191
"Yet, you have crossed it in the end."

390
00:21:36,150 --> 00:21:39,153
Should I tell everyone now?

391
00:21:40,154 --> 00:21:42,615
That might be better
than waiting around worried.

392
00:21:43,241 --> 00:21:44,575
Someone else will tell on me.

393
00:21:47,328 --> 00:21:48,371
Or should I just…

394
00:21:50,373 --> 00:21:54,001
DO YOU WANT
TO DELETE THIS NOVEL?

395
00:21:56,796 --> 00:21:57,797
[sighs]

396
00:22:04,512 --> 00:22:05,513
Jenny.

397
00:22:07,723 --> 00:22:08,766
-Hi.
-Hi.

398
00:22:12,478 --> 00:22:15,189
Did you know someone in our class
writes web novels?

399
00:22:15,815 --> 00:22:16,816
Really?

400
00:22:17,692 --> 00:22:19,485
You and Eui-ju were talking about it.

401
00:22:21,529 --> 00:22:22,989
Oh.

402
00:22:23,072 --> 00:22:26,075
So, I thought you'd know who she was.

403
00:22:26,659 --> 00:22:28,494
[chuckles] I have no clue.

404
00:22:28,578 --> 00:22:29,579
[amusing music playing]

405
00:22:29,662 --> 00:22:35,501
Well, it's a BL novel written
with our teachers as the main characters.

406
00:22:36,210 --> 00:22:37,461
Crazy!

407
00:22:38,504 --> 00:22:39,839
It will come out someday.

408
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:43,843
Nothing stays a secret forever. Right?

409
00:22:49,140 --> 00:22:50,224
[softly] Dang.

410
00:22:50,308 --> 00:22:51,976
[breathes deeply]

411
00:22:55,229 --> 00:22:56,439
Hey, Eui-ju, look.

412
00:22:56,522 --> 00:22:59,942
I took a pic of this cat
going to drawing lesson yesterday.

413
00:23:00,026 --> 00:23:01,110
Isn't it so adorable?

414
00:23:04,614 --> 00:23:05,990
What's going on?

415
00:23:06,991 --> 00:23:08,034
Mmm.

416
00:23:09,118 --> 00:23:10,453
[phone buzzes]

417
00:23:11,329 --> 00:23:14,373
[menacing music plays]

418
00:23:15,708 --> 00:23:16,709
SPECIAL OFFER FOR THE INTERNET

419
00:23:18,085 --> 00:23:19,212
[breathes deeply]

420
00:23:21,214 --> 00:23:22,506
-Hey.
-[gasps] Huh?

421
00:23:23,257 --> 00:23:25,885
You're acting really weird.
Something's going on.

422
00:23:26,385 --> 00:23:28,554
[sighs] Ugh, I already said no.

423
00:23:33,684 --> 00:23:35,978
Sorry. You startled me.

424
00:23:37,897 --> 00:23:39,774
Mm-hmm. Oh, okay.

425
00:23:44,695 --> 00:23:46,906
[Woo-su] All right, F of x…

426
00:23:48,366 --> 00:23:52,995
equals the integral of x
plus 3x square plus x cube,

427
00:23:54,664 --> 00:23:56,082
which is negative 10.

428
00:23:57,083 --> 00:24:01,045
Thus, f of minus 1 comes out
to negative 10. Not too hard, right?

429
00:24:01,128 --> 00:24:03,547
-[class] Right.
-[Woo-su] Let's call it a day here.

430
00:24:03,631 --> 00:24:04,674
Good job.

431
00:24:04,757 --> 00:24:06,509
[class] Thank you.

432
00:24:09,553 --> 00:24:11,138
-[students] Goodbye.
-[Woo-su] Bye.

433
00:24:19,563 --> 00:24:21,399
Mr. Ga, I have a question for you.

434
00:24:23,359 --> 00:24:28,364
I get why C is 6 in problem number 356,
but I'm stuck on what to do next.

435
00:24:28,447 --> 00:24:31,409
-[Woo-su] Is this not doable for you?
-[Ha-su] It's a bit confusing.

436
00:24:32,285 --> 00:24:36,122
[Woo-su] If you integrate from here,
you get x cube plus 4 for g of x.

437
00:24:36,205 --> 00:24:38,749
Then, just evaluate g at negative 2.

438
00:24:39,959 --> 00:24:42,420
Keep in mind that the product rule
can be used this way, okay?

439
00:24:43,379 --> 00:24:44,547
-Okay.
-Good job.

440
00:24:44,630 --> 00:24:45,631
Oh. Mr. Ga.

441
00:24:49,343 --> 00:24:51,595
I brought this,
I thought you would like it.

442
00:24:54,015 --> 00:24:55,308
You didn't have to.

443
00:24:58,644 --> 00:25:00,604
Don't do it again, all right?

444
00:25:00,688 --> 00:25:02,023
Yes. Okay, sir.

445
00:25:05,234 --> 00:25:06,777
[Woo-su]
Do you find anything else difficult?

446
00:25:06,861 --> 00:25:08,821
-[Ha-su] Nothing else so far.
-[Woo-su] Good.

447
00:25:14,201 --> 00:25:15,244
You're still here?

448
00:25:16,787 --> 00:25:19,248
-Uh…
-I guess you have something to tell him.

449
00:25:19,332 --> 00:25:21,375
You should've asked
a question during class.

450
00:25:27,048 --> 00:25:29,133
-I'll be going, then.
-Bye.

451
00:25:38,434 --> 00:25:39,435
What is it?

452
00:25:43,147 --> 00:25:44,815
Mr. Ga, I think I'll have to…

453
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:48,861
take a break from writing the web novel.

454
00:25:51,197 --> 00:25:52,198
Why?

455
00:25:53,074 --> 00:25:56,118
Well, I need to focus on studying.

456
00:25:56,952 --> 00:25:59,789
And I keep skipping homework.
You know that.

457
00:26:23,938 --> 00:26:26,023
Why the lack of confidence?
It's not like you.

458
00:26:26,982 --> 00:26:29,485
That's not it. I'm wondering…

459
00:26:30,236 --> 00:26:32,571
if I should just take
a short break from writing.

460
00:26:34,448 --> 00:26:36,492
I don't know what gave you
that kind of idea,

461
00:26:37,368 --> 00:26:39,662
but think back to
when you first started writing it.

462
00:26:40,329 --> 00:26:42,623
Remember exactly
why you started the novel,

463
00:26:43,249 --> 00:26:45,126
the first intention that drove you.

464
00:26:45,209 --> 00:26:47,044
[tender music playing]

465
00:26:47,128 --> 00:26:48,337
The answer must lie there.

466
00:26:49,338 --> 00:26:52,466
If you actually want to quit writing,
or if it's just an excuse…

467
00:26:56,637 --> 00:26:57,888
to get better at writing.

468
00:26:58,889 --> 00:27:02,518
Wasn't that the reason
that you started this whole thing?

469
00:27:02,601 --> 00:27:05,104
[breathes deeply]

470
00:27:05,187 --> 00:27:07,523
I'm not sure
if it's the real reason, though.

471
00:27:08,023 --> 00:27:12,570
[sniffles] But I do feel a bit better when
I hear you put it into words like that.

472
00:27:17,491 --> 00:27:18,492
Here, cheer up.

473
00:27:22,705 --> 00:27:25,207
[ominous music playing]

474
00:27:25,291 --> 00:27:26,459
[gasps]

475
00:27:33,174 --> 00:27:34,175
[exhales sharply]

476
00:27:36,385 --> 00:27:39,180
[breathes shakily]

477
00:27:40,055 --> 00:27:43,017
[rock music playing]
